# Project Intelligence: MacOS Process Monitor

## Project Patterns

### Architecture Patterns
- Project follows a modular design with clear separation between core functionality and interfaces
- Core components communicate through standardized messages to facilitate future language migration
- Interfaces (CLI, GUI, web) share the same core functionality but with different presentation

### Implementation Patterns
- Python with psutil for initial implementation
- Core functionality designed with language-agnostic principles for potential future Go or Rust implementation
- Simple data structures (dicts, lists, primitives) used for easy translation to other languages

### User Experience Patterns
- Command-line interface for initial functionality
- Future GUI interface planned using PyQt/PySide
- Future web interface planned with Python backend and HTML/JS frontend
- All interfaces should provide consistent functionality and user experience

## Project Preferences

### Code Structure
- Clear separation between core functionality and interfaces
- Modular design with well-defined component boundaries
- Comprehensive docstrings and type hints
- Tests for all core functionality

### Configuration
- YAML-based configuration with sensible defaults
- Support for user-specific configuration overrides
- Command-line options for overriding configuration settings

### Logging
- Structured logging with timestamp, process information, and resource usage
- Log rotation to manage disk usage
- Multiple log levels (INFO, WARNING, ERROR)

## Project Evolution

### Current Phase
- Initial setup and architecture design
- Focus on core functionality implementation

### Future Phases
- Command-line interface implementation
- GUI interface implementation
- Web interface implementation
- Potential migration to Go or Rust

## Known Challenges

### Cross-Platform Considerations
- Initial focus on MacOS
- psutil provides cross-platform capabilities if needed in the future
- Core architecture designed to be platform-agnostic

### Performance Considerations
- Minimize monitoring overhead
- Efficient process data collection
- Optimized log writing and rotation

### Interface Considerations
- Consistent experience across multiple interfaces
- Shared core functionality with different presentation layers
- Efficient communication between components
